article.headline: Marist's sharp shooting overcomes sloppy play to beat St. Peter's
article.linkText: Fitz posts double-double to lead Marist to victory
article.story:
POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. --  Rachele Fitz had 22 points and 11 rebounds as Marist (No. 21 AP) cruised to a 78-58 victory over St. Peter's on Friday night.

Fitz scored in double digits for her 51st straight game and helped the Red Foxes (16-1, 7-0 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) to their 13th straight win. Though sloppy at times, Marist shot 58 percent from the field, including 46 percent from 3-point range.

Julianne Viani scored 18 points and Erica Allenspach added eight points and six assists for the Red Foxes, who have allowed fewer than 60 points in eight straight games.

Tania Kennedy led St. Peter's (4-11, 1-5) with 22 points, and Natasha Morris added 10. The Peahens shot just 36 percent.
